cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the privacy and analysis of search logs, which falls under the categories of cybersecurity (cs.CR), databases (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and cryptography (cs.CY). The paper proposes a technique for sanitizing search logs while maximizing output utility, which involves optimization models and randomization strategies. These techniques are relevant to all of the aforementioned categories, making it likely that the paper could be classified under any of them. However, given the focus on privacy and data analysis, cs.CR and cs.DB are the most likely categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.IR, and cs.CY.
